Analysis of terrorist activities around the world in 1970 - 2017 years¶

This is my analysis of data set of global terrorism below.¶

Data downloaded from: Global Terrorism Database

The database GTD is an open-source database including information on terrorist attacks around the world from 1970 through 2017. The next lines contain accurate data on carried out terrorist attack, such as: date, location (country, region, city, the exact geographical coordinates), number of killed and wounded, name of the terrorist group and its method of attack.

Context¶

Before I opened this data, I hadn't really realized that terrorist attacks are not isolated incidents which may occur once every few years!!

The purpose of my analysis is to show you that terrorism is a serious global problem. I used Python programming language together with special libraries (numpy, pandas, matplotlib) to explore the most interesting data. Don't be afraid :) - I won't overwhelm you by an enourmous amount of boring numbers and statistics. I also put some data visualization into my analysis.

import pandas as pd
import numpy as np
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import seaborn as sns

data = pd.read_csv('globalterrorismdb_0718dist.csv', encoding='ISO-8859-1')

data.rename(columns={'iyear':'Year','imonth':'Month','iday':'Day','country_txt':'Country','region_txt':'Region','city':'City','attacktype1_txt':'AttackType','target1':'Target','nkill':'Killed','nwound':'Wounded','summary':'Summary','gname':'Terrorist_group','targtype1_txt':'Target_type','weaptype1_txt':'Weapon_type','motive':'Motive'},inplace=True)

data = data[['Year','Month','Day','Country','Region','City','AttackType','Killed','Wounded','Target','Summary','Terrorist_group','Target_type','Weapon_type','Motive']]
data['Casualties'] = data['Killed'] + data['Wounded']

The most active terrorist groups and their "favourite" attack method:

In [24]:
series = data.loc[:,['Terrorist_group', 'AttackType']] #Selecting a sub-table of interesting columns
scolumn = series.loc[:,"Terrorist_group"] #Get one column with the group name
values_counts = scolumn.value_counts()
lvalues = values_counts.keys().tolist() #Get list of values
lcounts = values_counts.tolist() #Get list of counters


noRow = data.shape[0] #Number of rows in whole data

minimal_count = 2000 #Choosing the most active groups

print("Terrorist group | The most often attack method | Count\n")

for i in range(0,len(lvalues)):  #View terrorist group      
    
    if lcounts[i] < minimal_count: continue #Irrelevant group               
    
    gName = lvalues[i]
    
    if gName == 'Unknown': continue #Irrelevant group               
        
    #Creating dictionary of attacks for terrorist group    
    loc_dictio = dict()        
    for j in range(0,noRow):  #View attacks for the terrorist group
        loc_gname = series.iat[j,0]        
        if (loc_gname==gName):
            loc_attack_name = str(series.iat[j,1])                        
            if (loc_attack_name) not in loc_dictio:                    
                loc_dictio[loc_attack_name] = 1 #New attack  
            else:                
                loc_dictio[loc_attack_name] += 1 #Incrementing given attack

    maxCount = 0
    maxName = ''
    for k, v in loc_dictio.items(): 
        if v > maxCount:
            maxName = k
            maxCount = v        

    print(gName,"|",maxName,"|",str(maxCount)) #Display information: terrorist group with its the most often attack method and count
